Day in OOS: 13 shellings near 10 Ukrainian cities and towns
02 Nov 2019, 06:33 by Bogdan Petrishin





On Friday, November 1, 2019, armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries violated ceasefire 13 times in Donbass


This is stated in the press service of the Ministry of Defense of Ukraine.
"The enemy fired on the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with the prohibited Minsk agreements of 120 mm mortars, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns and other small arms," - the message said.
Russian-terrorist troops were firing near the following 10 settlements:

Starognatovka - 120 mm mortars, machine gun anti-tank grenade launchers (LNG) and large caliber machine guns;
Talakivka - from small arms;
Novogatovka - from anti-tank grenade launchers;
Water, that in the Azov region - from small arms and hand anti-tank grenade launchers;
Marinka - LNG and small arms;
Mayorsk - from anti-tank grenade launchers;
Lugansk - of large caliber machine guns and small arms and hand anti-tank grenade launchers;
Novolugansk - made of hand anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
Farm Free - from large caliber machine guns;
Trinity - automatic grenade launchers.
Yesterday, November 1, there were no casualties as a result of firing by the Allied forces.

From the beginning of this day, the armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries did not show any fire activity.
There were no casualties among the Allied forces.
